description: A clandestine meeting proves to be a trap for Arthur and Merlin when they are taken captive by a squad of Marauders led by Lt. Broons. The Marauder regime is very interested in Arthur and the implications of his return. With help from Mr. Rice Arthur, Merlin escape with Damon and Julia, two members of a resistance group called the Fort Nels. The group make it as far as the entrance to the Fort Nels camp when they are swarmed by a pursuing pack of Marauder zombies.

Down the Rabbit Hole

Dominic Green has a problem: He sees dead people. Specifically, the dead people that paid him to make them dead (It's a futuristic dystopia thing)

So far he's done a pretty good job of ignoring it.

But that's about to change.
name: Down the Rabbit Hole

description:
Nothing makes sense...everything that Doctor Spektor has ever known is called into question, and he'll stop at nothing to uncover the secrets and lies that hide beneath the surface of reality. Can the Master Of The Occult overcome his fears, and learn the unfathomable secrets of the universe? Only the legendary MARK WAID (Daredevil) and NEIL EDWARDS (X-Factor) can tell you...

description:
The Sound of Justice

Tectonic Zombies! SWAT Police! Flamethrowers! All these and so much more in this aaaaall-new episode of Fearless Man!
name: The Sound of Justice

description: In brief, Gutters is a series of standalone pages that parody the comic book industry and the heroes and characters that dwell within. Think of it as an editorial cartoon targeting comic books, and you'll understand where we're going with it. Gutters is written by Ryan Sohmer, with Lar deSouza as Art Director and Ed Ryzowski serving as colorist. As for who will be doing the actual art, well, that's where things get interesting (and slightly different). Rather than have one artist pencil each page, we elected to have a rotating roster of professional artists, among them some giants in the comic book industry alongside new and emerging talent.

This issue is about the descent into the great eternal Night - the foundation stone of Evil. Alex White is in trouble and Siddhartha has to strike the evil right in its roots! Will he succeed - a single torch of light in an opressing sea of darkness?...
name: The Growth of Light Within

description: A friendly visit to a local hospital sheds some light on Burma's mysterious business, Ninth World Enterprises. When Allison investigates further, however, she comes across the company's questionable origins. Could sweet Burma be hiding something truly sinister? Find out in this chapter of writer Paul Tobin (Bandette, Colder) and artist Benjamin Dewey's (The Tragedy Series) latest cat chronicle!
name: Chapter Five

description: New artists CARLOS PEDRO (Fast & Frightening) and STEVEN DENTON (Dept. of Monsterology) join writer/creator GEOFFREY D. WESSEL as the saga of psychotic footballer Scott Winslow continues through the gritty streets of East London, and the hallowed halls of justice...

The Truth is Told in Shades of Grey

Our first story arc comes to its mind blowing conclusion.

description:
Something to do with DEATH!

The only thing standing between Nick, Lou, and a romantic evening was one last errand for Nick's auto-mechanic boss. It was supposed to be a simple matter of seeing whether an ole wreck was worth restoring...but it turned into a confrontation with the cultists and a deepening of the mystery around Nick's parents' disappearance.
name: Something To Do With DEATH!

description:
Attack of the Nazi Mummies!

The Nazi alchemist, Kapitan Kreatur, has captured the Moses Militia. Can the team escape from the villain's underground base and stop him from assassinating the Allies' top leaders?
name: Attack of the Nazi Mummies!

description: Meet the number two killer in Zero's organization. No one knows his name, as he only reveals it to those he is about to kill. Trapped between the apparent conflict between Max and Naja, Number Two sees his opportunity to eliminate both of them to earn his proper place in the syndicate, only neither of his opponents are about to give up without a fight...
Even more sin is unearthed in this digital exclusive edition complete with sketches, a variant cover gallery and more! Find out the secret history of the Unseen! What is the Original Sin?
name: The Secret History of Colonel Nicholas J. Fury

description:
The Paper (Crane) Chase

A car accident rocks the peaceful halls of Kitty Country Day! With danger lurking for all of their classmates and students around the school, the Panther Scouts see an opportunity to help the community -- and to earn a valuable new badge. It'll take all their creativity and skill to teach their class how to be safe in the street, and one of the scouts may pay the ultimate price.
name: The Paper (Crane) Chase

description: Rumor 5: A silly tale of Princess Ai shrunk to chibi-size, a tragic tale of religious fervor, and a fine romance make for more perspectives on Ai's story!
name: Rumor 5

volume.name: Princess Ai: Rumors From the Other Side

description: While Henrys off in Louisville on a photo-shoot for famous TV reporter Megan Velez, he gets the surprise he least expected -- Punky showing up at the studio! Megan has some advice for a glum Punky you have to fight for what you want in life. Punky takes it to heart shes ready to stand up for what she wants! Only one problem the Family Court judge isnt about to take advice from an 8-year-old!
name: Oh, Shoot

description:
Night's Plutonian Shore

Nightwatcher Corvan Moore is literally on the brink of death. His daughter, Anastasia, guides him into the Veil of the Otherworld where he witnesses the horrible event that befell his family. An exchange with the id-ravens of his subconscious will set Corvan on his next path to find answers--and he won't like what he discovers.
name: Night's Plutonian Shore

description:
All Eyes On Me

Aria tracks down the Shaman to get more Soul Cage. But under Shaman's quid pro quo deal, Aria will find herself against a killing machine in a battle to the death.
name: All Eyes On Me

description: The third issue of Return to Rander gives insight into who our savior was. A search ends abruptly for Blane and Jameson, and timing seems to be bad for Layla.

Bayside is abuzz once the news that Americas Next Pop Diva is coming to town! Kellys ready to become a star Too bad shes completely tone-deaf. The whole gang wants to support her audition anyway, but the producers are a lot more interested in a goofy kid & his talking robotthats right, Kevin & Screech are the ones destined to become stars!

The Sentinels regroup and travel to Hell to save their missing teammate, Sin.

But before they can succeed, they must conquer the darkness within their own souls. All while the fallen angel, Damien, awaits them.

In Not Today, a desperate message sends Melania to a nursing home for one last chance to meet with an old flame. In Part One of Midnight Jack, a masked terrorist detonates a building under construction, declaring war on a drug manufacturer. The big company hires Tomboy and the others, putting the SideChicks on a collision course with a cold-blooded killer.
name: Not Today; Midnight Jack, Part One

description: Lex Luthors trapped Ted Kort and Michael Holt inside their Antarctic base, cutting them off from Booster Golds help.
name: Chapter Five

description:
Chapter 4 pt 4

The group is found out but Seth has a plan to get them all out.
name: Wild Things Part 4

description: After risking everything to enter the heavily fortified Tiklopis Way Station in search of his spaceship, Bops is devastated to find it has gone missing once again. Sha'A La's pod of Scroungers might hold the key to its recovery, but only if they are still alive. Bops, Max and Sha'A La make a desperate subterranean search for the Scroungers with Overlord Jardu Krush's ferocious Volk on their trail, while Amir and Marko make a daring last stand against Krush's Shock Troops. It's do-or-die time for Bops, with the fate of Centroa hanging in the balance!

Among the Early Snowdrops

After gliding away from their icy homelands, our Silent Little Monster Friend finds themself hundreds of feet up, stuck in a tree! But they're not alone! What is this new... 'thing'? And why does it keep throwing acorns at our Silent Little Monster Friend?

SUNRISE #2 follows on directly from SUNRISE #1, but this time with twice as many pages!
name: Among the Early Snowdrops

description:
The Longest Season

Tart is closer to learning why the Earth itself is freezing to death. Even if she can stop the demon behind it, will she be able to cure the damage that's already been done.
name: The Longest Season

description: INVINCIBLE JOE just wont let up! Hes getting tougher and tougher on Mayuri and shes absolutely had it. Will Joes hard core training drive Mayuri away? If so whos gonna pilot Trimaxx? The answers may lie with BIG JOHN ADAMS!

The Undertaker Morton Stone and his faithful hound, Cryptoe are on the trail of the tosser Mr. Noddy.

Little do they realise that Nod, the Toe Nail Clipper Killer, is on the lookout for Morty as well! Can the Undertaker get to split Noddy's corpus callosum with his spade, while avoiding that pesky a-hole Lt. Aubrey Turgid? Does Morton's spunky sister Sophie have all the clues? And are they all prepared for the dark, manky road they will have to travel to get to the munted truth?
Elena, Caroline and Bonnies plan to avenge a professor murdered by a werewolf gets into sticky territory when they infiltrate a party full of the frat brothers who had something to do with it!
name: Frat Pack Part 2 of 3

description: Kurt Busiek's classic reboot on Vampirella from 1991 ushers her into the modern age in "Vampirella: Morning In America!" We discover that Pendragon is still alive and on the road with his fifth rate magic show and heading for Washington. Adam and Vampirella continue their relationship and plan their attack on the Unseelie Congress. Vampirella discovers to her horror that the Cult of Chaos have published over four million copies of the the Crimson Chronicles in an attempt to gain more members. Nathan Shroud's plan is revealed. His interest in Chelsea was to try and create a new "Vampirella" to slay the other members of the Unseelie Congress. Each time Vampirella kills a member of the Congress, Nathan becomes more powerful. To assist him, Nathan summons a powerful demon - Bane.

Kurt Busiek's classic reboot on Vampirella from 1991 ushers her into the modern age in "Vampirella: Morning In America!" Vampirella discovers where Chelsea is being held. She, Adam and Pendragon fight undead warriors to free Chelsea. In the battle Pendragon uses "real" magic, which he has been learning to supplement his slight of hand. Chelsea is rescued and they discover Conrad Van Helsing, barely alive (despite the fact that they had buried his corpse in the last book!). They leave, unaware that Nathan Shroud has been watching and that their actions are fulfilling his complex plans.

Kurt Busiek's classic reboot on Vampirella from 1991 ushers her into the modern age in "Vampirella: Morning In America!" Nathan's plan to absorb the Unseelie Congress' power and rule the world himself is revealed. Vampirella finds Chelsea and they fight. Adam and Pendragon arrive and Adam stakes Chelsea. They realise that they have been lured into another trap as nathan reveals himself ...

The New York Times bestselling novel now adapted into comics, featuring full-color illustrations by Hugo Award-nominated artist Jimmy Broxton, and as adapted by fan-favorite writers Jimmy Palmiotti and Justin Gray. This contemporary dystopian classic--hailed by Justin Cronin, New York Times bestselling author of The Passage, as "an epic feat of imagination"--will captivate readers both familiar and new. This is the story of mankind clawing for survival, of mankind on the edge. The world outside has grown unkind, the view of it limited, talk of it forbidden. But there are always those who hope, who dream. These are the dangerous people, the residents who infect others with their optimism. Their punishment is simple. They are given the very thing they profess to want: They are allowed outside. in Issue #3 of 6: Juliette learned a little knowledge is a dangerous thing--but the whole truth is a death sentence...

Clouds gather on the horizon for the people of Argos. Their newborn prince, the son of Perseus, was stolen right out of his cradle. Perseus has fought many mythic monsters but never absorbed such a painful blow. Summoning all his strength and cunning, he goes out in search of his first-born and heir. This brings him back into the murky world of the three hags who possess the key that will help Perseus find his son. But information comes at a dangerous price: acquire the Horn of the Cyclops. As dangerous as this task is, Perseus is unaware of the mounting peril that seems intent on stopping him.

A new volume begins with the launch of Guardians of the Galaxy! Marvel's cosmic movie heroes are here at last! Guest-starring Iron Man!

By Brian Michael Bendis and Steve McNiven.

A shocking new series begins: Avengers Arena! Teenage superhumans are trapped in a kill-or-be-killed world!

By Dennis Hopeless and Kevin Walker.

Daredevil is marked for death by a mysterious new assassin: the man called Ikari!

By Mark Waid and Chris Samnee.

description: Its a rematch between Batman and Lord Superman. Is Terrys secret weapon enough to take down this super-powered madman?
name: Justice Lords Beyond: Another World, Part 8 of 8: Aftermath

description: A new weekly series begins, featuring the complete run of the original Batman manga created in the 1960! Batman and Robin face the evil Lord Dead Man.
name: Lord Death Man, Chapter 1 of 3

volume.name: Connie by Frank Godwin: The Menace of Mo Tung

name: The Life and Times of Ned Christie, Cherokee Patriot and Renegade

description:
Anthology

A charity book benefiting the Pancreatic Cancer Action Network featuring the talents of Tom DeFalco, J.M. DeMatteis, Ron Marz, Andy Lanning, Rick Leonardi, Vito Delsante, Cory Hamscher, Richard Clark and more.

The Asteroid Comics Magazine

The Asteroid is a quarterly superhero/science fiction orientated comics anthology. It serialises various separate stories in each issue, until each story arc is complete and a new story enters the universe. Join MAAK 'The ALL Knowing' as he glides through the universe telling tales from the Asteroid about energy being superheroes like 'The Blue Comet', or a samurai sword wielding cowboy like 'Rawhide Bushido'. It's a BIG universe, and there's something out there for everyone.

Just under one hour till sundown, the autumnal silence is ripped apart by screams, which won't be heard by any of the dwellers of the village nearby. Among these not-so-fertile fields, another predator nails down his defenseless prey...

Bear, Bird and Stag Were Arguing in the Forest (and other stories) contains the brand new 20 page title story as well as three of Madleine Flores's popular webcomics: Weave, Soul, and Wander.

In the days of talking animals, Bear, Bird and Stag argue over which one of them should be king. They seek the wisdom of the mystical Forest Witch, who sends them on a quest to prove how royal they are.

These four stories show Madleine's versatility as an artist and read with a sense of wonder often brought on by fairy tales.

volume.name: Bear, Bird and Stag Were Arguing In the Forest (and Other Stories)

description: The door behind Beth makes a small sound and closes, and she freezes The country cottage she is renting has a spring-loaded lock, and she's gone outside in her pajamas with her dog in the middle of the night and is now stuck outside. Not knowing what else to do, she sees a car passing by and waves it down for help. The man driving the car is Travis Black, who is tall and handsome. But considering Beth has just gotten out of a relationship with an unfaithful man, another love affair sounds inconcievable...
name: Vol. 1

description: Detective Daniel Credence has a gold shield and some dubious morals. This first book in the series is driven as much by Danny's struggles to find his place in a society gone insane as by the cases he cracks under deep cover.
name: Part 1

description:
Put me in, Coach!

The Peanuts gang is ready to play ball in this collection of baseball-themed cartoons. Some of the most popular Peanuts moments happen on the field and they're gathered here for a season full of enjoyment. As manager of the endlessly losing team, Charlie Brown soldiers on to keep his team's spirits up, while being constantly blown off the pitching mound in a clothes-exploding fashion. It doesn't help that his catcher is a musician by nature or that his shortstop is a dog. Not to mention that center-fielder Lucy can't keep her mouth shut long enough to know what's going on in the game! Put them all together and you get a game plan for laughs!

First published in 1950, the classic Peanuts strip now appears in more than 2,200 newspapers in 75 countries in 25 languages. Phrases such as "security blanket" and "good grief," which originated in the Peanuts world, are now part of the global vernacular, and images of Charles Schulz's classic characters-Charlie Brown kicking the football, Lucy leaning over Schroeder's piano-are now universally recognized.

Note: The digital edition (7/1/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: TPB

volume.name: Charlie Brown: POW!: A Peanuts Collection

description: Clown tells of former-journalist Jared Bastian who now makes his living as a clown in a roaming circus. When a group of revolutionaries attempt to spread their agenda during his performance, Jared puts a forceful stop to them and finds himself at the center of the Empire's attention.

New York City...a blizzard...the world in ruin...the undead fill the city streets. Those few lucky enough to survive the initial wave of undead lie huddled together in power deprived buildings high above the streets. Kolin Fleet and his small band of survivors seek to get out of the city before the snow thaws and the zombies are roaming free once again. Unfortunately, King Zombie has other ideas. All new story set in the Deadworld universe written by Mike Raicht (Marvel's ZOMBIE and SAVAGE TALES). Collects issues 1-4.
name: TPB

description: Death Hawk: You can hire him, but can't buy him...until now! This collection features the 25th century salvage expert and his protosymbiotic partner (an intelligent blob of goo) called Cyke that is connected to his body. The hard-luck heroes and the beautiful but treacherous con-artist Vanessa Bouvier find themselves unwilling partners as they engage in a quest to discover the secrets behind the ancient alien race known as the Skril and the sole surviving relic of their culture - the mysterious Soulworm. Death Hawks wry vision of the future includes giant worker ants, super-samaurai, bloodthirsty chicken-men, and a whole planet of people bioengineered to be perfect...as well as murderous. Featuring art by Adam Hughes. Foreword by New York Times best-selling writer, Douglas Clegg. If you're a fan of Joss Whedon's Firefly, the art of Adam Hughes or just good ol' blaster-blazing space opera, Death Hawk: The Soulworm Saga is a must-have!
name: Volume One

description: Princess Aliyah arrives to her wedding in a black wedding dress. This is a declaration of war to her husband, King Kamal. Seven years ago, the two were in a relationship, but he messed around with her and then left her. Now, the two of them end up in an arranged marriage, and she is being forced to give him an heir. Aliyah treats him coldly during the ceremony and that resistence awakens something within him. As the drums pronounce them husband and wife, Kamal takes Aliyah into the depths of the palace into his bedroom. Unable to hold himself back anymore, he rips off her black dress...
name: Vol. 1

description:
Aquariums and Restaurants

After a complete and total mental breakdown,-- Bob quits his day job at a fast food restaurant. He sticks a paper bag over his head and decides he's going to try and save the world.
name: Aquariums and Restaurants

description:
Book One

Murder in BC leads to an inuksuk in Ontario. Charlie's childhood friend is about to die. Hitchhiking in BC PJ's luck runs out. Lionel is in crisis, time for love? Leslie is a therapist and part time drug dealer. It's just occurring to her that she hates her job. Dan's six year old daughter thinks he needs to grow up. She may have a point.

Life is connections and causes you never see coming. The story of five friends confronted with failed dreams and fantasy lives. Learning to deal with traumas to their minds, bodies, and ideals.

First in a two part story, 161 pages of cinematic, neorealist comics by Salgood Sam. Exploring identity, destiny, and life in a possibly ambivalent universe.
name: Book One

volume.name: Dream Life: A Late Coming of Age

description: The legendary warrior of medieval Spain whose battles were a precursor for the upcoming Crusades in Europe and the Middle East are told in this graphic novel. In this chronicle, the life of El Cid is explored as he attempts to bring together both Moor and Christian into a unified Spain. Banished from his own Kingdom, the 'Cid' continues to fight, at various times on the side of both Muslim and Christian to bring a nation into being. Written by award winning author Gary Reed and amazing painted full color images by acclaimed noted artist Wayne Reid.
name: TPB

description: The biggest super team since the X-Men comes the white hot music sensation One Direction! For the 1st time, the two issues of the Fame One Direction join forces in one giant-sized graphic novel. See what One Direction is a British-Irish boy band consisting of members Niall Horan, Zayn Malik, Liam Payne, Harry Styles and Louis Tomlinson have been doing with their FAME in comic book form!
name: TPB

description: Today is the day Frankie has been looking forward to her whole life! It's her 16th birthday and she is all set to inherit her adult super powers, then the world will be hers! ... or will it?

Melbourne City.

A sprawling metropolis built upon the foundations of what was once known as the state of Victoria.

Globalisation has seen governments crumble and private corporations rise to rule and police their own sectors.

For those that live within the fortified walls of these corporate utopias life can be good.

But for the less fortunate there just exists the day to day struggle; Trying to eek out an existence in a volatile and dangerous world.

Superpowered 'Alphas', unchecked technological advancements, and a society where traditional morality is a long forgotten concept.

The future is a dangerous place and there are so very few that will stand up for the common folk.

Yet, in the face of such adversity, sometimes there are those who will make a stand for what is just...

... and their wrath will rain down upon the wicked.

The Lukewarm War

"The Lukewarm War" introduces us to Crusher Rondovich, an ex-Soviet spy. Now in America, he finds himself again caught up in an international plot.

The country is in turmoil as the 'Possess the Foundations' movement marches on the Capitol and a war hero is forced from the Marine Corps he dedicated his life to.

And somewhere in a hidden lab, an amoeba has mutated.
name: The Lukewarm War

description: A personal story about bullies, karate class, and wanting to learn how to kick butt.

The Girl Who Fell To Earth

In which two magical girls are born and much ado is made about virginity.
name: The Girl Who Fell To Earth

description:
An AGE OF DARKNESS crossover title! The countdown to GRIMM FAIRY TALES #100 continues! Sela has been faced with many unstoppable enemies, and she has always beaten the odds... but how can she survive an onslaught from all of her greatest foes at once? As Robyn, Shang, and Gideon race to save Sela, the villains of the Grimm Universe join together for a plan too horrible to imagine. PART TWO of the FOUR-PART STORY LEADING INTO GRIMM FAIRY TALES #100!

description:
Beatfghter Part 1

In the near future after the days of the earth razing event known as 'The Crippling,' humanity has survived by taking refuge in overcrowded city fortresses run by corporations at the cost of their freedom. While most are content to live in the gutter, some dream of the stars.

At the lowest level of this colossal citywork known as Dendrite, corporate backed terror gangs police the decaying streets with undisputed authority as they enforce their own twisted version of the law to any citizen they deem guilty. Amongst this cesspool of corruption lives Davron and Reno, two childhood friends turned brutal rivals who chase fame, fortune and freedom in the underground Beatfighter circuit; an illegal sport mixing music with a perception-heightening drug called bile. This candy colored world of infinite rhythm and Reach call out to Davron until the real world intervenes. In order to keep his mother and younger brother safe, Davron must face the ultimate prize fighter, his arch-nemesis, Reno. Will music alone be enough to save his family and his home?
name: Beatfighter Part 1

description:
Menace of the Mannequin - part one

Three powered individuals find themselves coming together to face a new kind of villain - the mysterious Mannequin!
name: Menace of the Mannequin Part One

description:
It Girl

"It Girl" is a black and white mini comic based on the life of silent movie screen star Clara Bow. In the Twenties, Clara Bow's star rose faster and shone brighter than any other Hollywood icon's. She epitomised the glamorous flapper... living fast, dancing the night away, stealing the heart of every man and becoming the role model for every young film fan.

Jessica's love of all things film and vintage has inspired her upcoming original graphic novel "Elsie Harris Picture Palace" previewed in the other half of "It Girl". Elsie is a young London girl dreaming of working in the film industry in the 1930s.
name: It Girl

person_credits.name: Jessica Martin
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, letterer, cover, other

description:
"Honkies From Outer Space Invade the Green Planet"...So Rude and Crude, they MUST be From Another Planet!

Graphic novel written, illustrated and hand-lettered by Wm. J. "Bill" Krupinski; Color covers, B&W interior artwork, 240 pages.

"Outlandish aliens invade the sustainably low-tech planet of Verdea, as it's endearing inhabitants employ music, crystals and quick-witted cooperation to stave off impending doom in an enjoyably bent, twisted and outrageous ride through a mind-meld of engaging original art, poetic prose and madcap characters in this compelling and creative graphic novel."

volume.name: Honkies From Outer Space Invade the Green Planet

description:
House Party marks the graphic novel debut by award-winning illustrator, Rachael Smith.

House Party follows three 20-somethings Michelle, Siobhan, and Neil, who are having trouble adapting to live in the real world since feeling like superstars at university. In an attempt to get their carefree composure and happiness back they throw a massive house party, just like they used to. Instead of reconnecting them with their younger selves, however, things go a little differently. In a story that will resonate with the 'lost' generation, we watch them try to move forward in lives that none of them really asked for.
name: GN

description:
Mystery at Kradmoor

The year is 1933. The place, the Carpathian Mountains of Eastern Europe. Pulitzer-prize-winner Molly Sloan and her intrepid assistant Timmy Mendez are hot on the trail of her next award-winning story when their contact is assassinated right before their eyes. But when a mysterious (and handsome) stranger assassinates the assassin, Molly and Timmy find themselves in over their heads...

Oh, hey, there's more Intergalactic Nemesis in the form of audio dramas, podcasts, a PBS Digital web series, and a live theatrical production. Visit www.theintergalacticnemesis.com to join in!
name: Mystery at Kradmoor

description: An illustrated primer to the most infamous serial killer in history! The shocking unsolved murder of five prostitutes in Victorian London ripped apart the society of the civilized world and led to incredible social changes. In this narrative of sequential comic pages, facsimiles of letters and notes, pictures from the time period, a survey of the social setting, the victims, the investigators, and the possible suspects are all explored. An informative insight into the world terrorized by Jack The Ripper.

What the Heck am i?

A forced vacation banishes land developer Jonah Kelly from his corporate life in Chicago. He reluctantly goes with his wife to her family's home on Oahu where he immerses himself in his father-in-law's business. Then one morning, he wakes up submerged in the ocean, transformed into a sea monster! Is he now banished to the sea?
name: What the Heck Am I?

description:
A full-color comic reader based on LEGO(R) Friends--a buildable play world for girls!

All the friends are all signing up for new activities at school! Andrea joins the chorus, and Stephanie makes the soccer team. But when Andrea's first concert is the same night as Stephanie's big game, Olivia, Emma, and Mia are torn between which event to go to. Can they figure out a way to cheer on both of their friends?

Sometimes Dead Just Isn't Dead Enough

NOIR meets SCI-FI in the 1st of a 4 issue series: A cop becomes guardian of a gateway to the beginning and end of the universe.
name: Sometimes Dead Just Isn't Dead Enough

description:
BOOK ONE : SOLE INVITATION.

Peter Campbell, the Writer, Artist and Creator, describes the story: LONE STAR SOUL is tale of a Black Mad Max walking across the sprawling sands of a distant desert planet, on a search for his Long Lost Soul - using old Soul Tunes as his guide.
name: Sole Invitation

description:
Fire from the sky

When a massive ball of fire erupts in the sky above Losstaria, the life of Marcus, son of Hector the blacksmith, changes forever. Marcus makes an incredible discovery that alters the fate of the kingdom.
name: Fire From the Sky

description:
Before he was the Devil, He was Lucifer Morningstar. Brightest of all the Archangels, Marshall of Heaven. This is the story of his Fall.

At the dawn of creation, existence was a raw, untamed frontier. Seven gunfighting Archangels defended the town folk of Heaven from Daemons, primordial beasts dwelling in the void beyond. They strove to carve out a civilization from the chaos of the naked universe, but the greatest danger they faced was not from the wilderness. It was from within.
